snippet.textDisplay:
900Watts average!!! that is awesome if you look at it in terms of average power.
Lets say we just take the energy spent during the up phase of move. the bar weighs 61.5kg, so the force exerted is about 603N.
Lets say the max height is 2.5m.
total energy spent is : 30x603x2.5 = 45225J
Average wattage is 45225/50.9 = 900Watts!!!
Eddie develops enough power to run an average toaster for 50.9 seconds!
He is a beast!!
PS: I know it is only an approximation but it was easy to do for this exercice (Elise) and quite a fun fact to know 😁
